DWL Keybind Cheatsheet (Super + /)

Window Management
-----------------
Enter                  → Open terminal (kitty)
d                      → Launch application menu (rofi -show drun)
e                      → Open file manager (thunar)
b                      → Open browser (xdg-open http://)
m                      → Quick Launch Mpv player with highlighted/copied link (quickmpv)
v                      → Clipboard manager (cliphist-rofi)
n                      → Dismiss notifications (makoctl dismiss -a)
a                      → Define word (define)
Shift + S              → Screenshot region (snip)
F5                     → Restart kanshi & enable adaptive-sync
Right                  → Focus next window
Left                   → Focus previous window
Shift + B              → Toggle status bar
i                      → Increase master area windows
p                      → Decrease master area windows
h                      → Shrink window horizontally
l                      → Expand window horizontally
Return                 → Zoom window
Tab                    → Switch to previous workspace
Shift + A              → Toggle gaps
q                      → Close focused window
f                      → Toggle fullscreen
Ctrl + Space           → Set previous layout
Ctrl + t/f/m           → Set tiling / floating / monocle layout
Shift + Space          → Toggle floating
0                      → View all Workspaces / tags
Shift + )              → Tag all windows
,                      → Focus monitor left
.                      → Focus monitor right
Shift + <              → Move window to left monitor
Shift + >              → Move window to right monitor

Workspaces / Tags
-----------------
1..9                   → Switch to workspace 1..9
Shift + 1..9           → Move focused window to workspace 1..9
Ctrl + 1..9             → Toggle workspace view
Ctrl + Shift + 1..9    → Toggle window tag on workspace

Power / System
--------------
Ctrl + Alt + p          → Power menu (kitty -e powermenu)
Ctrl + Alt + Backspace  → Quit DWL
Ctrl + Alt + Fx         → Switch VT (1..12)

Mouse
-----
Left click on layout symbol  → Set layout
Right click on layout symbol → Set layout
Middle click on title bar     → Swap windows around (zoom)
Middle click on DISK/RAM/CPU/TIME    → Open terminal
Super + click on client       → Move/resize window (Left = move, Right = resize, Middle = toggle floating)
Click on tag bar               → Switch/toggle tags
